It depends.
If you write scala or any functional language and you do pattern match it&#x27;s sometimes more readable if you have something like<p><pre><code>    blabla match {
        case 1 => func1
        case 2 => func2
    }

</code></pre>
instead of<p><pre><code>    blabla match {
        case 1 => 
            println(&quot;1&quot;)
            1 + 2
        case 2 => biggerFunc
    }</code></pre>
